	     <table class=mform  border=0 cellpadding=1 cellspacing=0 width=100%>
	     <form action=/cgi-bin/mrate.pl name=f105006410625007>
	     <tr><td id=headerrow colspan=2 class=mform valign=top><a name=>&nbsp;</a><a id=sj href=>races</a> <a id=fs8 href=#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a>
	     <br clear=all><small>Posted @ Fri, Apr 11th 9:05 AM 2003</small></td></tr>
	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=210295><span id= >jivehead</span></a><br><span id=notbold>6 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [3.00]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>Here's my opinion on the off chance someone might care.&nbsp;&nbsp;Ogres are very tempting to be as SK's, however, when picking a race i think alot of people put too much stock into starting stats.  Yes it's good to have, but at higher levels most stats can be raised fairly easily.  That said, I don't feel too much importance should be placed if you're deciding between ogre or troll.  As a shadowknight with very limited healing capabilities, the HP regen trolls offer is invaluable, unless you like sitting there playing Gems for an hour while healing or crying like an elf for someone to please come heal you.  So, I would pick troll over ogre for most any melee type class.  Plus i think the post luclin models for ogres are HORRIBLE.  They all look identical, and very lacking in detail. </p>&nbsp;<br> </td></td></tr>
	     <tr><td colspan=2 align=right class=mform id=fs8>3 Replies</td></tr>
	     </form></table><tr><td colspan=2><ul><table border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0><tr><td>
	     <table class=mform  border=0 cellpadding=1 cellspacing=0 width=100%>
	     <form action=/cgi-bin/mrate.pl name=f105057858360606>
	     <tr><td id=headerrow colspan=2 class=mform valign=top><a name=classes.html?class=5&mid=105057858360606>&nbsp;</a><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=5&mid=105057858360606>RE: races</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=5&mid=105057858360606#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a>
	     <br clear=all><small>Posted @ Thu, Apr 17th 8:00 AM 2003</small></td></tr>
	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=52194><span id= >Rexz</span></a><br><span id=notbold>182 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [2.99]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>I'll throw in my 2cp on this subject too. It's very true, there really is no race that stands out superior over another race when playing at high levels. All races has it's advantages and disadvantages. The very best advice I believe would be to play a race you like based on their &quot;LOOKS.&quot; Look at some of the highest SKs on your server of all the different types of races. If you see one that don't look good to you but were thinking about creating a SK of that race because they have nice starting stats or abilities such as regen, I would reconsider because there are items and enhancing features that will help you to acquire that gift. All you have to do is throw some AA points into Innate Regeneration at level 51 and Natural Healing at level 55 and you'll get your regen affect. <br><br>At the high end game, there are items you can get that can allow your SK to overcome a any handicap. If your character is huge, you can obtain an &quot;Anizok's Minimizing Device&quot; and shrink yourself regularly. If you play a gnome SK, there's also a &quot;Anizok's Maximizing Device.&quot; If youre a human type (such as myself) and hate their vision (which I do...LOL), there's the &quot;Mask of Draconic Enhancement&quot; that has the permanent effect of ultravision and see invisable. If you want 5K unbuff hitpoints, there are plenty of gears and armors to obtain to help you get there. Same with AC, STA, INT, etc. Anything can be obtain to help you reach your goal in this game. <br><br>However, there is only one thing you can never change no matter how uba you are or how strong your guild is in helping you to obtain an item you need. You can never change your race. If you don't like the way your SK looks wearing high level armors, there's nothing in the game that will allow you to change that. Until Verant decides to give SKs illusional masks like the ones that bards gets, the race you decide on making stays permanent for better or worst.<br><br><em id=fs8>Edited, Thu Apr 17 07:26:35 2003</em></p>&nbsp;<br></td></td></tr>
